).

– Type i—thick subcylindrical S-chaetae, on all antennal segments (
Fig. 12
): 3–4 ventrally on Ant. Ia (
Fig. 3
), several grouped in ventro-externo-distal sensorial fields on Ant. Ib, II and III (
Fig. 4
), and 2–7 distally on Ant. IV (
Fig. 7
).

– Type j—short, pointed, bent S-chaetae (
Fig. 13
), 2–8 distally on Ant. II and 3–4 on Ant. III, located near sensorial area; not seen on Ant. Ib.

– Type k—thin, short, hyaline S-chaetae (
Fig. 14
), on the whole length of Ant. III and IV and a few ventrally on Ant. Ib and II, some larger and intermediate with type i, especially on Ant. IV.

– Type l—thin, long S-chaetae (
Fig. 10
), similar in shape and size to f-type mes, but blunt at the tip, thinner proximally and not straight, present ventrally on Ant. Ia and Ib.

numerous dorsally on Ant. Ib and II, few ventrally on Ant. Ib; absent on Ant. Ia, III and IV. Subapical organite of Ant. IV long, thick and slightly bifurcate (
Fig. 7
).

Subapical papilla of Ant. IV, devoid of "pin seta" (
Fig. 7
).

type l and 3–4 S-chaetae of type i (
